MAN(1)

NAME
    man - show SmallOS manual pages

SYNOPSIS
    man [section] name

DESCRIPTION
    man opens a plain text manual page from /usr/share/man and displays it
    with a small built-in pager.

    When section is omitted, man searches the common SmallOS manual sections
    in this order: 1, 8, 5, 7, 2, 3, 4, 6.

    Pages are intentionally plain text. SmallOS does not currently implement
    troff, mandoc, compressed man pages, apropos, or whatis.

SECTIONS
    1   User commands and shell built-ins.
    2   System calls.
    3   Library functions.
    4   Devices and special files.
    5   File formats.
    6   Games and demos.
    7   General topics.
    8   System administration commands and daemons.

PAGER KEYS
    Enter
        Advance one line.

    q
        Quit.

    any other key
        Advance one screen.

EXAMPLES
    man ftpd
    man 8 ftpd
    man 1 man
    man 7 smallos

FILES
    /usr/share/man/man1/name.1
        User command pages.

    /usr/share/man/man8/name.8
        System command and daemon pages.

SEE ALSO
    smallos(7)
